This paper is about sentiment analysis on Twitter using deep learning techniques. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers natural language processing and computational linguistics. The use of RNN models and classifiers also suggests a focus on machine learning, which could place the paper in categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
